mscModFrsDprsNetTpmProvTable.name: mscModFrsDprsNetTpmProvTable
mscModFrsDprsNetTpmProvTable.description: This group specifies the mapping from the defined transfer priority to the egress emission priority and routing class of service. The mapping of transfer priority to egress emission priority and routing class of service may be modified by the user. Any changes to transfer priority mappings take effect on new calls. Existing connections are not affected by changes to transfer priority mappings unless the service is reset by locking and unlocking the connection or resetting the card where the service resides.

mscModFrsDprsNetTpmEmissionPriority.name: mscModFrsDprsNetTpmEmissionPriority
mscModFrsDprsNetTpmEmissionPriority.description: This attribute specifies the egress emission priority at the Frame Relay interface. A value of 3 specifies the highest priority, whereas a value of 0 specifies the lowest priority.

mscModFrsDprsNetTpmRoutingClassOfService.name: mscModFrsDprsNetTpmRoutingClassOfService
mscModFrsDprsNetTpmRoutingClassOfService.description: This attribute specifies the routing class of service value to be used on a transport connection. A value of multimedia specifies the highest class of service and a value of throughput specifies the lowest class of service.

mscModFrsDprsNetTpmAssignedIngressBandwi.name: mscModFrsDprsNetTpmAssignedIngressBandwidthPool
mscModFrsDprsNetTpmAssignedIngressBandwi.description: This attribute specifies the bandwidth pool which is used to support this transfer priority at this interface. For FrNni, this pool is defined by provisioning attribute ingressBandwidthPool under the FrNni Ca component. For FrNni, the value of this attribute can be overridden at the interface level by provisioning attribute assignedIngressBandwidthPool under the FrNni Ca Tpm/n component
